;フラッシュ


It felt like the air had been knocked out of me.

At that moment, even I could clearly understand that the barrier had been closed.

The human world and that world were separated, and the connection was closed without a trace.

"...Hahaha, I wonder what kind of trick it is. She disappeared even though she wasn't even walking."

I muttered without intending to let anyone hear.

The forest was flooded with light, and after that, no one had any idea how they disappeared.

It was an inexplicable feeling, as if I was in a dream, as if I had been turned into some kind of monster.

"...Well, maybe it was all a dream."

The mountain hut was also burnt down, and there is nothing to show that they ever existed.

It is impossible that he met and lived with elves in a forest where humans are not allowed.

It wouldn't be like a convenient dream that the elf I met for the first time adored me.

No matter who I tell, I'm sure no one will believe me. Those happy days have now turned into a dream.

“…Uuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuuu…”

I fell to my knees on the spot.

I was lonely.

The days I lived with Hinata and the others felt like happiness, so I felt even more alone and miserable.

There will never be anyone else who will love me like that, before or after.

The world has closed.

Those happy days will never come back.

It disappeared along with the burnt-down mountain hut.

"...Don't go, please don't go."

I reached out my hand in the direction where Hinata had disappeared, and when I realized that my fingertips couldn't touch anything, I clasped my hand.

I was the one who couldn't take Hinata's outstretched hand.

The truth is, I wanted to be with you forever... until the end of my life.

However, I was afraid that I might make Hinata unhappy... No, that's not it. I didn't take Hinata's hand because I was afraid someone would blame me for making her unhappy.

Who could blame me?

I was just a coward.

The happier his memories with Hinata and the others were, the more he feared losing them.

I was just afraid of losing it.

...Because I probably won't be able to protect Hinata in this world. It would be so?

"I really wish you didn't go, Hinata."

No matter how much I lament here, there's no way it will reach Hinata now that the world has been cut off.

Hinata's voice calling me to be with me is still in my ears, but I was the one who couldn't answer it.

Until the very end, when the world was cut off, I remained indecisive, blaming others for not being able to choose anything.

I continued to mourn while kneeling on the ground.

