It's time to start your journey, and it seems like it's okay to feel a little cheerful.

I crossed the village and thought of the dark forest.

Didn't Ibara say that the human path was created because of me?

So this departure is for the elves.

In order to end the path of humans, I will not return to the forest, but will leave the village I came from and travel far away.

The idea that it was for the sake of the elves was terrifyingly comforting.

I personally knew this was just an escape, but I needed a comfortable excuse for myself.

There are too many memories here, this village, that forest.

The weak me, the indecisive me, torments me here and there.

I know that running away won't change anything.

That's why I run away. But to a place that is not here.

Ibara asked me if that was okay. Hinata's voice stretched out her hand towards me until we parted.

No, it wasn't just that time.

I didn't even try to fit in with the people around me, and tried to maintain my ego by despising them.

A valuable record that was under fire because of that.

I'm running away from everything I've lost.

The only person beyond that is probably me, no one else.

That's okay though.

It would be better for me to live my life being chased by my useless self than to face my pathetic past self here, in this village.

Will I ever find my place?

If you wanted to change somewhere, would you have been able to change?

That day will probably never come, but I'm sure the memories I let go of will someday be beautifully colored in a way that suits me.

That's how I live by deceiving myself. We live in vain until one day we lose our lives. Not here. In a place out of reach of those happy days.

I will live my life forever feeling regretful about Hinata's hand that I was unable to take back then.

That must be my punishment for not being able to choose anything until the very end.


